World oil prices dropped despite a new hurricane approaching the Gulf of Mexico.
OPEC promised to increase crude supply if needed.
New York's main contract for October delivery fell to $66.30 per barrel.
Brent North Sea crude for November delivery also decreased.
Hurricane Rita strengthened to a category two storm with winds of 100 mph.
Airlines suspended flights due to the storm.
Evacuations were ordered in Louisiana and Texas as Rita threatened the Gulf Coast.
Emergency services evacuated residents of New Orleans again.
The Texas coastal county of Galveston issued a mandatory evacuation.
Overall, preparations were made as Hurricane Rita posed a significant threat to the region.
